---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
	title="Privacy Policy | App Trust Proxy"
	description="Privacy policy for the App Trust Proxy website and privacy-friendly analytics."
	bodyClass="sub-page privacy-page"
>
	<section class="page-hero">
		<div class="page-hero__inner">
			<img src="/app-trust-proxy-icon.png" alt="" width="88" height="88" decoding="async" />
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p>
				This policy explains what the App Trust Proxy website collects and how privacy-friendly analytics are used.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section__inner narrow legal-content">
			<p class="section-kicker">Last updated July 9, 2026</p>
			<h2>Website analytics</h2>
			<p>
				App Trust Proxy uses Plausible Analytics through analytics.apptrustproxy.com to understand aggregate website usage and improve the public website and documentation.
			</p>
			<p>
				The analytics script does not use cookies, browser local storage, or persistent cross-site identifiers. It is not used for advertising, profiling, or selling visitor data.
			</p>

			<h2>What is measured</h2>
			<p>
				Plausible records aggregate page views, referral sources, browser, operating system, device type, and approximate location derived from the request IP address. The raw IP address is not stored by Plausible.
			</p>
			<p>
				This site also enables Plausible outbound link tracking. When someone clicks a link that leaves apptrustproxy.com, Plausible may record the external URL and the page where the click happened as an aggregate event.
			</p>

			<h2>How this information is used</h2>
			<p>
				Analytics are used to see which pages are useful, where documentation needs improvement, and which outbound project links are used. App Trust Proxy does not use this data to identify individual visitors.
			</p>

			<h2>Third party links</h2>
			<p>
				The website links to external services such as GitHub. External websites have their own privacy practices, and this policy applies only to apptrustproxy.com.
			</p>

			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				For privacy questions about this website, contact the project owner through the public App Trust Proxy project channels.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>
